 {"id":"frankenjax-a4q","title":"Make UBS pre-commit gate actionable for inline-test-heavy Rust files","description":"Validation on frankenjax-wvj showed that the required UBS changed-files scan exits non-zero on touched Rust files mostly because inline test modules use ordinary assert, expect, and explicit panic patterns. Investigate a repo-local fix that preserves UBS signal while making the pre-commit rule practical: either reduce the highest-value panic surfaces in touched test code, or establish a scoped/configured UBS invocation that stays strict for production code without treating ordinary unit-test assertions as hard failures.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T20:25:15.960445647Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-08T03:19:11.593869891Z","closed_at":"2026-04-08T03:19:11.593631530Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"frankenjax-a7xi","title":"Harden cache golden verifier against truncated snapshots","description":"The fj-cache golden stability harness in crates/fj-cache/src/stability.rs verifies expected cache-key snapshots by zipping the supplied golden vector with the current generated vector. That silently ignores length mismatches, so a truncated golden snapshot can pass without checking newly added reference cases. It also ignores description mismatches, so reordered or renamed golden entries can produce confusing drift reports. Fix verify_golden_keys to report reference-count mismatches and per-index description mismatches before digest comparison, then add regression tests showing truncated and renamed golden snapshots fail. Validate with rch cargo test -p fj-cache stability, rch cargo check -p fj-cache --all-targets, rch cargo clippy -p fj-cache --all-targets -- -D warnings, cargo fmt --check, and ubs on the touched file.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:40:58.327214108Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:41:04.927678815Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
